citeinfo.title: AMCO On-Site Air Monitoring Points, Oakland CA, Live 2017, US EPA Region 9

descript.abstract: This feature class contains points depicting locations and air monitor sensor readings for Vinyl Chloride, Trichloroethene (TCE), and Tetrachloroethene (PCE) and supports the AMCO Chemical Superfund Site air monitoring process. Data are a subset of live sensor readings from the USEPA ERT Viper System and are updated in near real-time using ArcGIS GeoEvents. The features include links to archived sensor readings. Full metadata record can be found here:A HREF="https://edg.epa.gov/metadata/catalog/search/resource/details.page?uuid={28B6F2E3-B39E-465C-A95A-FE70297948CA}
descript.purpose: These data provide support for the EPA non-time critical removal action (NTCRA) at the AMCO Chemical Superfund Site located in Oakland, California to address the portions of the Site with the highest concentrations of volatile organic compounds (VOCs) that pose a threat to human health or the environment. During the cleanup process, a series of live air monitoring sensors are used to ensure operations are protective of human health. The air monitoring status is available to the public at https://epa.maps.arcgis.com/apps/MapSeries/index.html?appid=2e0a0e3d5cc041feb0c19d9f04327bcb.
